texts.text: >Megakin's group soon joins Shiang Sun and the others.
Sorry for the wait, guys! Help has arrived!
You finally made it. We're on our last leg here.
I had to cancel my concert rehearsal for this.
You all owe me BIG time.
We'll pay ya back with interest.
So, how's it lookin'?
Vince and the others are fighting hard elsewhere.
And damage has been minimal thanks to the other branches.
Still, widespread demon reports indicate a sizable army.
They're even in the mountains, so that's a definite yes.
Minimal damage despite multiple demons... How interesting.
It's as if their objective isn't to attack or conquer humanity.
If that giant lady's actions are any indication, I'd say—
Hold that thought.
Imma hungry! Wanna eat!
Snacktime! Snacktime!
The cavalry has arrived.
There's a lot of them. Brace yourselves!
Ugh, enough already! They just keep comin'!
The commotion must have attracted nearby demons.
Say what?! At this rate, we'll be here forever!
Isn't there a faster way to take 'em out all at once?!
If there were, I'd mention it—
Hmph!
*Yelp*
*Scream*
Huh?
Traitorous winged vermin. You fools waste my time.
*Shout*
>The demon newcomer swings his weapon down in a wide arc.
>The slash attack splits every demon in half.
What a powerful demon.
Who is this guy...?
Looks like all the demons have been eliminated.
Cool. Let's take five.
So, Mr. Helper Demon.
Since you're still here, I take it you've got business with us?
That is correct, humans—no, Liberators.
So, you've heard of us.
I am Nergal, lord of the underworld.
I've come to your world in pursuit of our world's Tiamat.
Tiamat... You mean the giant demon that appeared in Odaiba?
Wait a sec. What's this about "your world" and "our world"?
Are you from another world?
Not again...
Yes, this looks like yet another interdimensional incident.
Indeed. You catch on quickly.
We've got lots of experience.
Yeah, unfortunately.
Why has Tiamat come to our world?
She's likely on a manhunt...no, a demonhunt.
In the video, she rambled on about killing Marduk.
As I recall, he's a Babylonian god.
Correct. Tiamat intends to slay Marduk.
Long ago, he and a host of other gods murdered her.
However, Tiamat and her furious spite have been newly reborn.
She's a hideous, vengeful monster and a disgrace to our world.
Marduk and the others have come in preparation to defeat her.
Huh? Then, that mess just now...
Was all 'cause Marduk and his friends dropped by?!
They could've done this at home...
I understand your frustration. That's why I've come.
There will only be further casualties if we wait for Marduk.
Therefore, our best option is to defeat Tiamat first.
You're askin' for our help?
Yes.
Tiamat is powerful, but we can win if we work together.
You must think pretty highly of us.
Teamin' up with a demon like you, huh?
What should we do, Megakin?
Sure, why not? Let's go for it. He's a powerhouse.
Somethin's up. 'Sides, we don't even know this random demon.
Still, he did help us just now.
I'll put my trust in him for now.
We should prioritize Tiamat's defeat and resolve this matter.
Besides, if we work as a team...
...Yeah, I hear ya.
We'll go along with your plan, Nergal.
But if I think you're actin' the least bit shady...
Very well. After all, Tiamat's death is my only objective.
I expect great things from you.
It'll be pleasure to fight alongside you, Nergal.
Right, we should head to Tiamat's location in Odaiba.
Yeah, about that.
I bailed on rehearsal, so I'll catch up after a quick call.
Then I'll stay right here as your bodyguard!
No thanks. Go ship yourself to the deli, swine.
Yes ma'am! I shall eagerly await your return pre-sliced!
Okay. Catch ya later, Shionyan.
The coast is clear, Kokoro.
Tadaaaa! Super Priestess Kokoro, reportin' for duty!
...Could you BE more annoying?
Oops, sowwy. I'm just an entertainer at heart.
Huh? Where is everyone?
They went on ahead.
One problem at a time, but you can't be too careful.
I need you to look into something for me.
